.TH "HTMLTEMPLATEELEMENT.SHADOWROOTCUSTOMELEMENTREGISTRY" "3JS" "February 23, 2026" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
HTMLTemplateElement.shadowRootCustomElementRegistry \-
HTMLTemplateElement: shadowRootCustomElementRegistry property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]shadowRootCustomElementRegistry\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]HTMLTemplateElement\f[R] interface reflects the value of the
\f[CR]shadowrootcustomelementregistry\f[R] attribute of the associated
\f[CR]<template>\f[R] element.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This property is not useful for developers, and is only
documented for completeness.
If a \f[CR]<template>\f[R] element is used to declaratively create a
\f[CR]ShadowRoot\f[R], then this object and property do not exist.
Otherwise, if an \f[CR]HTMLTemplateElement\f[R] is created, the value of
this property is irrelevant because the object is not a shadow root and
cannot subsequently be changed to a shadow root.
.RE
.SH VALUE
A string that reflects the \f[CR]shadowrootcustomelementregistry\f[R]
attribute of the associated \f[CR]<template>\f[R] element.
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
